# Widget & Screen Conventions

## UI/UX Mindset

Think like a 40-year veteran frontend architect who has shipped products used by millions. Every screen you create should feel polished, intentional, and professional â€” not like a tutorial project. Consider:

- **Visual hierarchy**: The most important content catches the eye first. Use size, weight, color, and spacing deliberately.
- **Micro-interactions**: Subtle animations (via `flutter_animate`) make the app feel alive. Fade-ins, slide-ups, shimmer loading â€” these details separate amateur from professional.
- **Whitespace**: Generous spacing breathes life into layouts. Cramped UI feels cheap.
- **Consistency**: Every screen should feel like it belongs to the same family. Same padding rhythms, same card styles, same typography scale.
- **Edge cases**: Empty states, error states, loading states â€” handle them all with the same care as the happy path. An empty feed with a beautiful illustration and encouraging message is better than a blank screen.

## Naming

- **Screens**: suffix `Screen` (e.g. `FeedScreen`, `SettingsScreen`)
- **Shared widgets**: prefix `Nubar` (e.g. `NubarButton`, `NubarAvatar`, `NubarTextField`)
- **Feature widgets**: descriptive name without prefix (e.g. `PostCard`, `StoryBar`)
- **Private helpers**: prefix `_` (e.g. `_SectionHeader`, `_ThemeSelector`)
- **Files**: `snake_case.dart` matching the primary class name

## Screen Template

Every screen should follow this structure:

```dart
class FeatureScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  const FeatureScreen({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final colorScheme = Theme.of(context).colorScheme;
    final textTheme = Theme.of(context).textTheme;
    final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context)!;

    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(title: Text(l10n.featureTitle)),
      body: // content
    );
  }
}
```

## Standard Widgets

| Purpose | Widget | Package |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Loading | `LoadingIndicator` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Error | `NubarErrorWidget(message, onRetry)` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Empty state | `NubarEmptyState(icon, title, subtitle)` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Avatar | `NubarAvatar(imageUrl, radius)` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Button | `NubarButton(text, onPressed, isLoading)` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Text input | `NubarTextField(controller, label)` | `shared/widgets/` |
| Network image | `CachedNetworkImage` | `cached_network_image` |
| Paginated list | `PagedListView` / `PagedSliverList` | `infinite_scroll_pagination` |
| Shimmer loading | `Shimmer.fromColors(...)` | `shimmer` |

## Forbidden Patterns

- **NEVER** use `Image.network()` â€” always `CachedNetworkImage`
- **NEVER** load all data at once â€” always paginate with `infinite_scroll_pagination`
- **NEVER** show raw exception strings to users â€” use `NubarErrorWidget` with l10n message
- **NEVER** use `Navigator.push` with anonymous routes â€” prefer named or typed routes

## Async State UI

Always handle all three states from `AsyncValue`:

```dart
provider.when(
  loading: () => const LoadingIndicator(),
  error: (error, _) => NubarErrorWidget(
    message: l10n.error,
    onRetry: () => ref.invalidate(provider),
  ),
  data: (data) => data.isEmpty
    ? NubarEmptyState(icon: Icons.inbox, title: l10n.noData)
    : buildContent(data),
);
```

## Images

- Always provide `placeholder` and `errorWidget` in `CachedNetworkImage`
- Use `BoxFit.cover` for thumbnails and avatars
- Constrain image dimensions to prevent layout overflow
